                    <h6 class="text-uppercase font-weight-bold">
                        <strong>Cosmic Explorer</strong>
                    </h6>
                    <hr class="deep-purple accent-2 mb-4 mt-0 d-inline-block mx-auto" style="width: 60px;">
                    <p>The name "Cosmic Explorer" comes from David McClelland of the Australian National University
                       and represents the project's goal to explore the Universe with gravitational waves.
The Cosmic Explorer artwork was created by Evan Hall and shows the large L-shaped detector on a vast open plane
 with black holes merging in the sky.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <!--/.First column-->

                <!--Second column-->
